<subSubSection box="[151,1358,1538,1565]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" box="[151,1358,1538,1565]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1538,1564]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male abdominal sternite VI with a pair of long processes nearly straight and divergent (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1345,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1574,1600]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[353,374,1575,1601]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[427,449,1575,1601]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
; not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authority="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda, 2021" authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" box="[865,983,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[865,884,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[897,983,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[989,1078,1575,1601]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[989,1078,1575,1601]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Head. Supracervical setae 4–6 per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Thorax. Anterior dorsocentral setae behind transverse suture. Prescutellar acrostichal setae absent; acrostichal setulae in 2 or 4 rows. Apical scutellar setae slightly more distant to each other than to basal scutellar seta.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" box="[199,1329,1719,1745]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Legs. Patch covered with only minute pubescence absent on anterodorsal portion of fore tarsomere I.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Abdomen. Male: sternites III and IV wider than long. Female: sternites III–V longer than wide; VI as wide as long, posteriorly dilated, medially notched on posterior margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1538,2033]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Male terminalia. Epandrium pubescent except for narrow anterior to ventral margin and anteroventral elongation, roundish on posteroventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[679,783,1863,1889]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus long, moderately broad plate with 5–6 recurved teeth apically and 1 trichoid seta ventrosubapically (
<figureCitation box="[762,870,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Median piece of subepandrial sclerite medially and anteriorly bilobed into long lobes. Cercus pubescent except for anterior margin and apical portion, slightly constricted ventrosubapically, with 34–36 setae all over and small setae on apicoventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1339,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath apically broadly round in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[666,768,2007,2033]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" startId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" targetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1424,1592]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1424,1448]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">FIGURE 18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Toda" authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" box="[293,553,1424,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vieti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[293,495,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Colocasiomyia vieti</emphasis>
Toda
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[562,642,1424,1448]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,642,1424,1448]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1638,2025]" box="[199,909,1638,1665]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Female terminalia. Oviscapt with 16–18 ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[792,896,1638,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1638,2025]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Indices (range of 
<typeStatus box="[399,497,1674,1700]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[553,588,1675,1701]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">3♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[644,679,1675,1701]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">3♀</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[687,800,1675,1701]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">paratypes</typeStatus>
): FW/HW = 0.54–0.57, ch/o = 0.43–0.56, prorb = 0.86– 1.03, rcorb = 0.44–0.52, vb = 0.34–0.47, dcl = 0.50–0.73, sctl = 0.65–0.83, sterno = 0.58–0.78, orbito = 0.64–0.89, dcp = 0.63–0.94, sctlp = 0.62–0.95, C = 2.08–2.39, 4c = 0.89–1.04, 4v = 1.46–1.70, 5x = 0.90–1.13, ac = 2.81–3.14, M = 0.36–0.47.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1638,2025]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Puparium (3rd instar larva). Anterior spiracle with stalk ending in a whorl of 9–11 branches; stalk longer than longest branch; caudal segments elongate, ending in Y-shaped posterior spiracles (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1205,1854,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 18E–G</figureCitation>
). Mouth hook: distal blade as long as basal portion, apically pointed, gently curved downward, with small, acute teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1353,1890,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Colocasiomyia vieti Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype, ♀ paratype, and puparium from Cuc Phuong, Nho Quan District, Vietnam). A, Periphallic organs (lateral view; inset: surstylus distal portion); B, phallic organs (lateral view); C, ditto (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view); E, puparium (ventral habitus); F, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, mouth hook; I, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D and I, 1.0 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766442/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 18H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
