<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda, 2021" authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" box="[588,708,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[588,607,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[622,708,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[715,806,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[715,806,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in many characters, but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic character and the absence of patch covered with only minute pubescence on anterodorsal portion of fore tarsomere I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
